d four out of seven in the men's.\", \"from\": 795, \"to\": 916, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 804, \"end\": 811, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"score\": 0.9999999991059667, \"rank\": 7.348593688690651e-10, \"text\": \"Ireland\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"fact\", \"from\": 798, \"to\": 802}, {\"ngram\": \"a boxer\", \"from\": 827, \"to\": 834}, {\"ngram\": \"every category\", \"from\": 838, \"to\": 852}, {\"ngram\": \"the women's competition\", \"from\": 856, \"to\": 879}, {\"ngram\": \"the men\", \"from\": 906, \"to\": 913}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And Aidan Walsh is now among the ten as he bounced back from defeat earlier in the tournament to come through the hard way by winning the four-fighter box-off in Bangkok.\", \"from\": 918, \"to\": 1088, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 922, \"end\": 933, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aidan_Walsh\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.214133287009199e-17, \"text\": \"Aidan Walsh\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aidan_Walsh\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aidan_Walsh\"}, {\"begin\": 1080, \"end\": 1087, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bangkok\", \"score\": 0.9999999999904503, \"rank\": 9.069890095110125e-12, \"text\": \"Bangkok\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bangkok\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bangkok\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"defeat\", \"from\": 979, \"to\": 985}, {\"ngram\": \"the tournament\", \"from\": 997, \"to\": 1011}, {\"ngram\": \"the hard way\", \"from\": 1028, \"to\": 1040}, {\"ngram\": \"the four-fighter box-off\", \"from\": 1052, \"to\": 1076}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Having won his semi-final on Saturday, Walsh secured a unanimous-decision victory over Angel Gabriel Llanos Perez of Puerto Rico to secure a berth in